  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dd9\u0da7\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dbd\u0dd3\u0da7\u0dbb\u0dca 33000\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc4\u0dcf \u0da9\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dbd\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dbb\u0dca 109000\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db4\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca \u0db7\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dba\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "33000 liters of petrol and 109000 liters of diesel in police custody",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the police, 33 847 liters of petrol, 19 634 liters of diesel and 19 214 liters of kerosene have been seized so far in the raids carried out by the Sri Lanka Police in protest against the illegal collection, storage and sale of fuel stocks.",
        "1077 raids have been conducted all over the island from 6:00 AM on April 11th to today (20th) 6:00 AM and this arrest has been made. The number of arrested suspects is 997."
      ],
